item.title: Tilted Content Slideshow
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: This slider plays with 3D perspective and performs some interesting animations on the right-hand side images.

item.title: Navigation
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: For the "line" navigation we use a little trick to make the clickable area a bit bigger: we add a thick white border to the top and bottom of the span. Since the border is part of the element, it will be part of the clickable zone.

item.title: Responsiveness
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: For smaller screens, the items on the right hand side will become less opaque and serve as decoration only. The focus will be on the description which will occupy all the width.

item.title: Column or Row
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The items in the tilted container are either laid out in a column or in a row. For some directions we need to adjust the animation delays for the items, since we don't want the items to overlap each other when they move in or out.

item.title: Tilted Items
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The perspective view is achieved by adding a perspective value to the slide list item and tilting a division that contains the two screenshots.

item.title: CSS Animations
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: We are using 12 different animations for showing and hiding the items of a slide. The animations are defined by randomly adding data-attributes called data-effect-in and data-effect-out for every slide.
